                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d657">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">341.1154L58/257: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-21T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >April 21, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 21—9:50
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>186. Department’s 152, April 17, 6 p.m.<note n="15" xml:id="d657fn15">Not
                        printed.</note> I called on Sir John Simon last evening by appointment to
                    discuss orally again the Lewis gun case <pb facs="0926" n="826" xml:id="pg_826"
                    /> with him as set forth in the Department’s instruction 255, February 20th. He
                    told me a written note was in process of completion, but for my information the
                    position of the British Government remained unchanged in this matter of a
                    Belgian corporation. In brief he gave me to understand that after a careful
                    review of the case upon receipt of the last American note (see my 548 of March
                    6) the British Government’s position was unaltered and would not consider
                    reopening the matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
